{"TopicId":182197,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Full controller support for PC?","CreatedByName":"KerbolExplorer","CreatedById":177191,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-15T20:02:24Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"KerbolExplorer","CreatedById":177191,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-15T20:02:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRecently i bought a Nintendo switch,and with that a pro controller.What that this have to do with KSP?keep Reading:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen i realized steam has pro controller support i inmidiatly began playing PC games with it.Surprisingly KSP doesnt support this on PC wich is extremly odd...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo\u00A0im saying why not add controller\u00A0support for PC?At least on steam.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"klgraham1013","CreatedById":105132,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-16T14:07:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey can\u0027t even get joysticks working on linux...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn Windows, you can use your\u00A0controller, but like basically every other game with\u00A0controller support, in KSP you have to map it out in the settings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PunkyFickle","CreatedById":130214,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-02-16T16:20:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, if your controller works through\u00A0Directinput, which is likely\u00A0the case if you can play other games, KSP will work. You just have to map your controls.\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ECheck if it shows as a game controller in\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cem style=\u0022color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EControl Panel\\Hardware and sound\\Devices and Printers\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E. (While you are here, you might want to calibrate it\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0right click and\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cem style=\u0022color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EProperties\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E,\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ci style=\u0022color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EGame controller\u00A0settings\u003C/i\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E,\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cem style=\u0022color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EProperties\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E,\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cem style=\u0022color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ESettings\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0and\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cem style=\u0022color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ECalibrate\u003C/em\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E.) Then just launch KSP and set your controls in the\u00A0settings.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAbout Linux, Taniwha just released an apparently (didn\u0027t test, don\u0027t run linux)\u00A0rather decent input API.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed469579876\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/182142-161-linux-wip-advanced-input-010/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}